cs|6|fp|1|va|2|at|^-{      Defense Vs Notrump - Comments by Howard Schutzman    }
^-|cs||fp||ht|c|AT|
^*B3) Comment about pulling penalty doubles^*N
As noted above, Howard is not a big fan of penalty doubles of 1NT. However, even if you decide to play them, Howard strongly disagrees with Cohen about what it means when you pull a penalty double. Cohen recommends you treat the penalty double as a strong NT and play "systems on" (e.g. 2C is Stayman, 2D is a heart transfer, etc.). The problem is the doubler often does not have a strong NT shape. So Howard recommends that all 2-level bids by partner of the doubler be natural and weak.|
